The Herald The National Arts Council, on behalf of the Ministry of Youth Sports Arts and Recreation, yesterday presented groceries and other consumables to popular Actor Lazarus Boora at his rural home in Rukweza in Nyazura where he is recuperating from the surgery he underwent last year. <img class="wp-image-469899 size-medium" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/Standing-With-NACZ-Deputy-Director-Josia-Kusena-and-Assistant-Director-Arts-Promotions-and-Programming-Barbara-Gotore-360x201.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="201" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/Standing-With-NACZ-Deputy-Director-Josia-Kusena-and-Assistant-Director-Arts-Promotions-and-Programming-Barbara-Gotore-360x200.jpg 360w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/Standing-With-NACZ-Deputy-Director-Josia-Kusena-and-Assistant-Director-Arts-Promotions-and-Programming-Barbara-Gotore.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Lazarus Boora standing with NACZ Deputy Director Josia Kusena and Assistant Director Arts Promotions and Programming Barbara Gotore The goods were presented to “Gringo” and his wife by NACZ Deputy Director Mr. Josia Kusena and Assistant Director Arts Promotions and Development Mrs. Barbara Gotore.